🏛️ Harvverse DAO: Governance Simulation (TestNet)This module documents the decentralized governance structure of Harvverse, currently operating in a simulated TestNet environment to validate community participation.🎯 Purpose & MissionObjective: To test and validate decentralized decision-making regarding sustainability, climate education, and Web3 governance.Mission: Foster a culture of inclusive governance and collective responsibility within the Harvverse regenerative metaverse.⚖️ Governance Model (Simulation Rules)Voting Mechanism: Direct voting where 1 Wallet = 1 Vote.Platform: Compatible with Aragon, DAOhaus, or Snapshot interfaces.Quorum Requirements:Minimum Quorum: 30% of registered members must participate.Approval: Simple majority (>50% of valid votes).Duration: Each voting period lasts 3 days.💰 Simulated TreasuryDuring this test phase, resources are represented by DAO Points (symbolic, non-monetary):Allocation: Each member receives 100 DAO Points to prioritize ideas.Usage: Points are used to support community activities, communication campaigns, and metaverse developments.











